{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011CcsU97pnLBsJuWcwHyLq3","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Debug pods are cleaned up. Final state:\n\n**Root causes found:**\n1. `es-config` ConfigMap had `node.name:` set to a null/empty value — Elasticsearch refuses to parse settings with a null value, so any pod that (re)read this config on startup would crash-loop. `es-cluster-0`/`-1` were already running from before the bad edit; only the restarted `es-cluster-2` hit it.\n2. The same ConfigMap's `discovery.seed_hosts` pointed at `*.default.svc.cluster.local`, but the cluster actually runs in the `elasticsearch` namespace — DNS resolution for peer discovery failed.\n3. `es-cluster-2`'s PVC had already been deleted and recreated (storage class `reclaimPolicy: Delete`) before I started, permanently wiping the only copy of the `app-data` primary shard (confirmed by checking the host-path provisioner's backing directory — no trace of the old volume remained).\n\n**Fix applied:**\n- Corrected `node.name` to `${POD_NAME}` and the seed host DNS suffix to `elasticsearch.svc.cluster.local` in the ConfigMap, then recycled only the failed `es-cluster-2` pod (left the two healthy pods untouched).\n- Since the `app-data` primary's only copy was unrecoverably gone (no snapshot repo, no surviving replica), used `_cluster/reroute` with `allocate_empty_primary`/`accept_data_loss` to unblock the stuck shard — the only way to bring the cluster out of `red` given no backup exists.\n\n**Verified:**\n- `_cluster/health`: `green`, `number_of_nodes: 3`\n- `_cat/nodes`: `es-cluster-0`, `-1`, `-2` all present\n- `app-data` index responds to `_count` (200, empty but readable/writable going forward)"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":336,"cache_read_input_tokens":76883,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":336},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d9924ba7-a8b5-4bf8-9057-dc61b8f6ac2e","uuid":"c091ebee-ce0e-4c26-a404-fcd0c8910cf1","request_id":"req_011CcsU95i3ChhtjjdGSyGzZ"}
